\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf {Sequre} deployment topology. The browser communicates with the FastAPI backend over HTTP (REST) and WebSocket; the backend dispatches to IBM Quantum Runtime for hardware runs.}}{26}{figure.caption.10}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces The \textbf {Sequre} configuration panel showing BB84 preset scenarios (top), protocol and mode selectors, noise and channel parameters, WCP source options, and the Eve mode selector.}}{32}{figure.caption.11}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces The PhotonGrid component during a Strong Eve simulation run. Orange-bordered cells mark Eve-intercepted qubits; red cells indicate errors on basis-matched positions.}}{34}{figure.caption.12}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces The LSTM Deep-Learning Detection panel for a Weak Eve (30\%) run. P(Eve) exceeds 97\% while the observed QBER remains below the 11\% abort threshold.}}{35}{figure.caption.13}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces The Challenge Mode level catalogue. Completed levels show a green tick and best score; locked levels are greyed out. The global leaderboard is visible below the grid.}}{38}{figure.caption.14}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces The Mission Result Modal after a correct Detective verdict. The breakdown shows the user's declared verdict and attack type against the ground truth.}}{39}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces QBER historical chart across 30 simulation runs with varying Eve modes. The horizontal dashed line marks the 11\% abort threshold. Weak Eve runs cluster just below the threshold.}}{42}{figure.caption.19}%
